1. Create new laravel project
    $ laravel new admin

2. Create new repository on github via cli
    $ gh repo create
        ? Repository name R2l-Admin
        ? Repository description Saas website
        ? Visibility Public
        ? This will add remote origin to your current directory. Continue?  Yes
        ✓ Created repository piyushgupta09/R2l-Admin on GitHub
        ✓ Added remote https://github.com/piyushgupta09/R2l-Admin.git

3. Initialise git repository
    $ cd admin
    $ git init
    $ git add .
    $ git commit -m "Laravel Installed"
    $ git push --set-upstream origin master
        Enumerating objects: 108, done.
        Counting objects: 100% (108/108), done.
        Delta compression using up to 4 threads
        Compressing objects: 100% (89/89), done.
        Writing objects: 100% (108/108), 68.49 KiB | 1.29 MiB/s, done.
        Total 108 (delta 6), reused 0 (delta 0), pack-reused 0
        remote: Resolving deltas: 100% (6/6), done.
        To https://github.com/piyushgupta09/R2l-Admin.git
        * [new branch]      master -> master
        Branch 'master' set up to track remote branch 'master' from 'origin'.

4. Create a new app on digital ocean platform
    - Choose github repository from list
    - Enter environment variables
    - Build command
